main event: Three strange blinking lights were observed crossing the path of an aircraft in flight in Syracuse, New York in August 1963.
interesting points: The lights were described as 'three strange blinking lights'.
The lights were observed crossing the path of an aircraft in flight.
The observer called the Air Force about the sighting.
The analysis on the Project Blue Book record card concluded that there was 'insufficient data for evaluation'.
The observer was a retired Air Force major who was interested in UFO sightings and had collected reports on the subject.
witnesses: civilian observer, retired Air Force major
